   676                                  
   677                                      ; === CR3 STRATEGY ===
   678                                      ; Previously: build page tables at 0x70000 and load CR3.
   679                                      ; This crashed on real AMD Zen 5 (Acer Nitro ANV16-42).
   680                                      ; New strategy: KEEP using UEFI's page tables (they already work).
   681                                      ; UEFI identity-maps all of low memory + framebuffer.
   682                                      ; We just need 0x0-0x200000 (kernel+stack) and FB mapped, which they are.
   683                                      ; Skip custom page tables entirely.
   684                                  
   685                                      ; Bar 10: DARK RED = keeping UEFI page tables
